parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat back screws can cause the seat backs to detach from the seat frame, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, particularly during sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: The seat back screws or shrouds break off
the seat back moves or comes loose
the driver and passenger are pushed forward against the steering wheel and dashboard
the seat back is no longer securely attached to the seat frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver's Side Seat Belt Extension Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side seat belt to extend can lead to improper restraint, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The driver's side seat belt does not extend
making it difficult or impossible to wear the seat belt properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Gas Pedal Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The malfunctioning gas pedal can also cause the vehicle to accelerate even after the driver has removed their foot from the pedal.
symptoms: The gas pedal feels strange or shifts to the right
the vehicle accelerates unintentionally
the vehicle continues to accelerate even after the driver has removed their foot from the pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to restrain the driver can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not hold the driver in place during an accident
allowing the driver to move around or be ejected from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Recall Repair Parts for Battery Fuse Block Inspection and Chassis Fuse Relocation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unavailable parts for the recall repair can put riders at risk, as the vehicle may experience steering and light failures, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to the unavailability of recall repair parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause critical safety features such as headlights, brake lights, and instrument panel lighting to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, the loss of power steering can make the vehicle difficult to control, leading to potential crashes.
symptoms: Headlights
rear brake lights
and instrument panel lighting randomly shut off
power steering seizes
steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
ABS warning indicator illuminates
traction control and steering ability fail
vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the control module can cause critical safety features such as ABS and traction control to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: ABS warning indicator illuminates
traction control and steering ability fail
vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery cable can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle will not start
battery cable is loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failure warning can cause the "brake failure" light to illuminate on the dashboard, disabling the cruise control and potentially leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The "brake failure" light illuminates on the dashboard
cruise control is disabled
brake pedal feels spongy or soft
brake pedal travels further than usual
vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.
